  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "We should introduce a buffer (similar to what we have in the webhook output backend) to the log file output backend. Audit events should be queued on a relatively large buffer chanel, and an output go routine should grab events off the queue and write them to disk. If an audit event is output when the channel is full, it should be dropped (this should be counted by a prometheus metric, and an e2e test should ensure that the count is below some threshold). This behavior should be optional (configurable)\r\n\r\n/cc @crassirostris \r\n\r\n~~Mitigates: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/51899~~ 51899 is tracking the `delete pods` regression",
